      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_SBMR_getPendingSBMRsList",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve a list of pending SBMR (Service Billing and Meter Reading) records from a database. It joins several tables to compile a comprehensive dataset that includes utility company details, agency information, facility numbers, and service addresses. The procedure filters records to include only those that are not marked as completed and orders the results by the SBMR reference number in descending order and then by the utility company."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity level of this stored procedure is considered medium. It involves multiple table joins, including inner, left, and right joins, which require a good understanding of the database schema and relationships. The use of a custom function "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "dbo.ConvertYYYYMMDDToDatetime",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " adds an additional layer of complexity."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "This stored procedure does not take any input parameters. It is designed to retrieve all pending SBMR records without filtering based on user input."
        }
      ]
    },
